nfo":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/ad1a017949674a947f0d6794cbf7130d642c6530/src/Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/Arith/CommRing/EqCnstr.lean#L223-L252","name":"Lean.Meta.Grind.Arith.CommRing.EqCnstr.toMonic","line":223,"kind":"def","docLink":"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/Arith/CommRing/EqCnstr.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.Arith.CommRing.EqCnstr.toMonic","doc":"Tries to convert the leading monomial into a monic one.\n\nIt exploits the fact that given a polynomial with leading coefficient `k`,\nif the ring has a nonzero characteristic `p` and `gcd k p = 1`, then\n`k` has an inverse.\n\nIt also handles the easy case where `k` is `-1`.\n\nRemark: if the ring implements the class `NoNatZeroDivisors`, then\nthe coefficients are divided by the gcd of all coefficients.\n"},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/Arith/CommRing/EqCnstr.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.Arith.CommRing.EqCnstr.toMonic\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Meta</span>.<span class=\"name\">Grind</span>.<span class=\"name\">Arith</span>.<span class=\"name\">CommRing</span>.<span class=\"name\">EqCnstr</span>.<span class=\"name\">toMonic</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/Arith/CommRing/Types.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.Arith.CommRing.EqCnstr\">EqCnstr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/Arith/CommRing/Util.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.Arith.CommRing.RingM\">RingM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/Arith/CommRing/Types.html#Lean.Meta.Grind.Arith.CommRing.EqCnstr\">EqCnstr</a></span></div></div>"},{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/ad1a017949674a947f0d6794cbf7130d642c6530/src/Lean/Meta/Tactic/Grind/Arith/CommRing/EqCnstr.lean#L213-L221","name":"Lean.Meta.Grind.Arith